.TH "regmap_fields_update_bits_base" 9 "regmap_fields_update_bits_base" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
regmap_fields_update_bits_base \- Perform a read/modify/write cycle a register field with port ID
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" regmap_fields_update_bits_base
.BI "(struct regmap_field *field "  ","
.BI "unsigned int id "  ","
.BI "unsigned int mask "  ","
.BI "unsigned int val "  ","
.BI "bool *change "  ","
.BI "bool async "  ","
.BI "bool force "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "field" 12
Register field to write to
.IP "id" 12
port ID
.IP "mask" 12
Bitmask to change
.IP "val" 12
Value to be written
.IP "change" 12
Boolean indicating if a write was done
.IP "async" 12
Boolean indicating asynchronously
.IP "force" 12
Boolean indicating use force update
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
A value of zero will be returned on success, a negative errno will
be returned in error cases.
